facilities enabling joint controls between neighbouring States (one-stop
technology), 24 hours a day, whenever justified by trade needs
and in line with road traffic regulations;

Border (interchange) stations where phytosanitary,
veterinary and other controls are carried out shall be provided with
technical equipment;

The carrying
and traffic capacity of border (interchange) stations and adjacent
tracks must be adequate for the volume of traffic;

Inspection areas must be available, as well as
warehousing for the temporary storage of goods subject to customs or
other forms of control;

